{
  "texts": [
    "Outliers or noisy data points can have a disproportionate impact on the imputed values.",
    "Impact of Outliers: Outliers in the dataset can significantly influence KNN imputation.",
    "If there are outliers, the nearest neighbors chosen for imputation may not be representative of the local data distribution, leading to inaccurate imputed values.",
    "Equal Weighting of Neighbors: KNN imputation assumes that all K nearest neighbors contribute equally to imputing a missing value.",
    "In reality, some neighbors may be more similar to the missing instance than others, but KNN treats them all equally."
  ]
}